1.1
log
@Correct indentation for lists and displays inside lists.

Inspired by a diff from millert@@, but implemented rather
differently and with slightly better functionality.
In particular, this one respects -offset and -width
arguments found in the input file.
@
text
@.Dd November 18, 2012
.Dt BD-NESTED 1
.Os OpenBSD
.Sh NAME
.Nm Bd-nested
.Nd nested displays and lists
.Sh DESCRIPTION
regular
text
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
outer
text (default indent)
.Bd -ragged -offset indent
inner
text (default indent)
.Ed
outer
text
.Ed
regular
text
.Bd -ragged -offset 4n
outer text (4n)
.Bd -ragged -offset 2n
inner text (2n)
.Ed
outer text
.Bl -tag -width 6n
.It tag
text
.El
outer text
.Ed
regular text
.Bl -tag -width 6n
.It tag
outer text
.Bd -ragged -offset 2n
inner text (2n)
.Ed
outer text
.El
